The paper discusses the construction of test suites for black-box optimization benchmarking, which is a topic that falls under the category of numerical optimization (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of single-objective problems to construct multiobjective problems, which is a topic that falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of the constructed test suites, which is a topic that falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
